transcript:
I'm a psychologist and he's my top five
signs of an anxious attachment style in
your relationship number five you find
it hard to trust them so you constantly
seek reassurance but sometimes your
partner sees that as controlling or
clingy number four you feel dependent on
your partner so when you don't have full
access to them it can bring up feelings
of anxiety or even jealousy number three
you have a low opinion of yourself and
feel worthless sometimes but you see
your partner in a much more positive
Light number two you only feel enough
when your partner shows you approval so
you're always striving to be whatever
they want you to be and number one you
tolerate unhealthy behaviors that you
know are toxic because you feel like if
it ends that would confirm that core
belief that you're somehow worthless or
unlovable
